│ make `combineOrders` robust against these invalid indices. The check `if (Order[Idx] !=    │
│ Sz)` is insufficient as it doesn't protect against values greater than `Sz`. Changing this │
│ check to `if (Order[Idx] < Sz)` will correctly handle both the `Sz` sentinel value and any │
│ erroneously large values, preventing the crash.\n\n```cpp\n//                              │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\n\n5931     if (Order[Idx] < Sz)\n5932     │
│ UsedIndices.set(Order[Idx]);\n```\n\nThis is a defensive fix. The true root cause is the   │
│ creation of the invalid index in `ReorderIndices` upstream, but this change prevents the   │
│ immediate crash and handles the invalid data gracefully.\n\n5. **Conclusion**: The         │
│ proposed edit corrects the faulty check in `combineOrders`, preventing the out-of-bounds   │
│ access that leads to the assertion failure. By ensuring that only valid lane indices (less │
│ than the vector width `Sz`) are used to set bits in `UsedIndices`, the function becomes    │
