╭─ Assistant [MainThread@2414474] ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ The previous fix, while solving the immediate crash, was too aggressive and caused a       │
│ regression by changing the vectorization output in a valid case. The analysis shows that   │
│ the logic in `combineOrders` for filling undefined lanes was flawed. When `Order[Idx]` was │
│ `Sz` (undefined), the original code would not mark any index as used. The new logic should │
│ have been to mark `Idx` as used if `Order[Idx]` is `Sz`, but only if `SecondaryOrder` is   │
│ empty, because that's the path where `Idx` would be used to fill the undefined lane.       │
│                                                                                            │
│ The correct fix is to handle the `Sz` case explicitly. If `Order[Idx]` is `Sz` and there   │
│ is no secondary order to provide a value, the lane at `Idx` will be filled with its own    │
