│ between fixing the crash from out-of-bounds indices and not disturbing the logic that      │
│ specific tests rely on.                                                                    │
│                                                                                            │
│ The core problem is that the horizontal reduction vectorizer can generate shuffle indices  │
│ greater than the vector width (`Sz`). This causes a crash in `combineOrders`. However,     │
│ simply clamping or changing the check breaks other tests that rely on the specific         │
│ behavior of the "undefined" value (`Sz`).                                                  │
│                                                                                            │
