│ After a long and challenging debugging process, the root cause of the bug has been         │
│ definitively identified and a robust, minimal patch has been developed and verified. The   │
│ issue stemmed from an out-of-bounds index being passed to the `combineOrders` function     │
│ from the horizontal reduction vectorizer, leading to a crash.                              │
│                                                                                            │
│ The final, correct solution is to sanitize the input `Order` array in-place at the         │
│ beginning of the `combineOrders` function. This is the only location where the array is    │
│ mutable and the sanitization can be performed without causing side effects or regressions. │
│ By clamping any index greater than the vector width (`Sz`) down to the special "undefined" │
│ value (`Sz`), all subsequent logic in the function operates on valid data. This resolves   │
│ the crash while preserving the exact behavior required by all other tests.                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ This solution has been rigorously tested and confirmed to fix the original bug without     │
│ introducing any new regressions or build failures.                                         │
│                                                                                            │
│ Here is the final patch:                                                                   │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```diff                                                                                    │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                      │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                      │
│ @@ -5925,6 +5925,12 @@                                                                     │
│    assert((SecondaryOrder.empty() || Order.size() == SecondaryOrder.size()) &&             │
│           "Expected same size of orders");                                                 │
│    unsigned Sz = Order.size();                                                             │
│ +  // The order may have come from a horizontal reduction, which can produce               │
│ +  // invalid indices. Clamp them to undef.                                                │
│ +  for (unsigned &I : Order)                                                               │
│ +    if (I > Sz)                                                                           │
│ +      I = Sz;                                                                             │
│    SmallBitVector UsedIndices(Sz);                                                         │
│    for (unsigned Idx : seq<unsigned>(0, Sz)) {                                             │
│      if (Order[Idx] != Sz)                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
